# Authentication

There is only one way to authenticate requests.  Requests that require authentication will sometimes
return `404 Not Found` instead of `403 Forbidden` to prevent leaking private data.  To authenticate a request
send an auth token in the `Authorization` HTTP header.  To retrieve an auth token see the <%= link_to('Login', '/users#login') %>
end point.

<pre class="terminal">
$ curl -H "Authorization: Token AUTH-TOKEN" https://api.example.com
</pre>


